    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:571
    old "She observes you with the patience of a statue, then sends the one-handed man outside with a nod. After a minute, she brings from the basement a simple package covered with wax, tied together with a couple of cords. She removes them in silence, the scent of honey fills the air. \n\nShe raises a dark cloak, green like trees covered by shadows. The shapes of leaves are embroidered on the surface with a silver-like thread, from the hood to the very bottom. They are the size of your hand, spread sparsely, elegant. Each one is different. \n\nIt’s heavy, most likely rainproof, but the inner layer is downy, made from lambswool. Every scrap of this garment was touched by a master. \n\n“There’s magic in it.” {color=#f6d6bd}Foggy’s{/color} voice is solemn. “Keeps you warm at night, without a fireplace. Makes rocks feel like fur.” "
