    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:2728
    old "“I never reached The Growing Mountains, even less so The Southern Realms. It’s a different world for me, but any folks from there are welcome at my place, no matter their tongue or looks. I mean, they are already among {i}our{/i} tribes, not as invaders, but as farmers and hunters. We’ve no right to bear them ill will after the emperors pillaged their lands for centuries.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:2741
    old "“I’ve never tried to reach the southern borders. Folks say the peaks there disappear into the clouds, and it takes strong lungs to cross even the gentle passes. There are tales I’ve heard in the capital and on my journeys, but no soul talks ‘bout The Growing Mountains now, not since the war. The clans stay hwere they always have been, and so does our forest.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:2754
    old "“I’ve seen only a small part of it, and there are not many journeys left in these bones!” She chuckles and points at her legs. “I don’t even know how large The Land is.” "
