    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:3605
    old "“I know a fair bit ‘bout that house, it’s not more than a few years old. It’s east of the watchtower, surrounded with a wall. My {color=#f6d6bd}Ilan{/color} helped build it, {color=#f6d6bd}Tzvi{/color} as well, as did many souls from {color=#f6d6bd}Gale Rocks{/color}. {color=#f6d6bd}Eudocia{/color} enchanted things for all the tribes for years, that’s how she got enough savings and trust to get the stone and wood she needed. She slept alongside the workers in the watchtower for months. {i}I can’t trust they’ll build it right{/i}, she told me.” \n\n“Now she doesn’t leave her home at all, just surrounds herself with walking rocks. She doesn’t seek friends among the tribes. Maybe she’s lonely. Or maybe crazy. A witch.” "
