    # game/areas/foggylake2foggy.rpy:3685
    old "“That old {i}gal{/i} from {color=#f6d6bd}Gale Rocks{/color} told me it’s {color=#f6d6bd}The Wanderer{/color}, a spirit who looks after travelers. She’s centuries old, the spirit, not the statue, and needs gifts, just a bit of this and that, to pay for her own food and shelter. At her feet, one should spare an apple, a dragon bone, even a pretty pebble. Those who skimp on her will one day be in need, and will see a woman with a staff on the horizon, too busy with her own struggles to help them.” \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}Foggy{/color} frowns, moving the scars on her forehead. “But how do we know hwat these travelers saw? Beats me!” "
