    old "She leans forward, but her voice seems to be incapable of a whisper. “You don’t plan to swim there, d’ye? You won’t get there without a boat. And {i}with{/i} a boat it’s still a dice roll, There’s always a drunk or two in {color=#f6d6bd}Rocks{/color} and {color=#f6d6bd}Howler’s{/color} who says they’ve been there, but it’s all rubbish, they hardly touched the island’s wall.” \n\nYou try to pressure her a bit, but don’t learn much. She claims that it’s high above the sea, on the top of a wall-like steep cliff, and “a rope may not be enough for one to get to the top”. From time to time, a pillar of smoke flies out of the volcano in the center of the island. “The whole place is green, with animals as great as dragons. Could it store treasures, like the folks say? Maybe. But no soul knows where to look for them. For all I know, some child started a tale and played with everyone’s desperate dreams.” "
